  "text": "The bene®ts of maintaining populations of native bird species in the countryside are twofold. First, this diversity is likely to supply valuable ecosystem services for humanity's sake, including aesthetic values, pollination, pest control and seed dispersal for the maintenance of vegetation cover and its associated bene®ts [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Second, while for many species there will be no substitute for extensive native habitats, the tropical countryside may provide substantial conservation opportunities for biodiversity's sake. This window of opportunity will close soon as pressures to increase food production intensify, unless biodiversity conservation is integrated explicitly into agricultural policy.",
